scripts.text:
The door of the library and the wall around it have been staved in. Smashed brickwork and shelving litter the floor, all covered by a fine layer of dust and mould.

Within, you see damage from battle and years of exposure to the weather. Torn and scorched books lie everywhere - what wasn't destroyed by fire and sack has succumbed to rain and mould.
Yet, in the far corner, you see a large coffer partly buried by debris...
You step over the bones of some poor scribe who appears to have died in defence of his books.
The ancient coffer has been blackened by fire, chipped and dented by the years, and is covered with dirt and mould.
Not far ahead, the road comes to an abrupt end in a large pile of stones. It appears that some sort of massive rock fall has blocked the way.
All you can find of the dragon's hoard is one small chest. Somewhat disappointing.
Little remains of this building. Weeds and mould sprout from the ruins.
The area around these remains is blackened and scorched.
